CORRECTION (supersedes mem-1781787710449 mtime/restart hypothesis): the gm-plugkit browser-witness client-edit-no-witness false-positive on src/cli.js had a SIMPLE root cause, not a restart re-baseline. In rs-plugkit src/browser_witness.rs, is_browser_running_file() classifies .mjs/.cjs/.js/.ts/.css/.scss/.sass as browser-running iff the path starts with a BROWSER_DIR_PREFIX, and that list INCLUDED 'src/' -- the universal Node CLI/lib/server dir -- so src/cli.js matched and any non-browser project editing src/*.js was blocked at COMPLETE forever (no page to page.evaluate). Fix landed at the source (rs-plugkit, where the wasm watcher code lives; auto-published via .github/workflows/release.yml -> plugkit-bin releases + gm.json bump): commit ca3cf12 removed 'src/' from BROWSER_DIR_PREFIXES (keeps .jsx/.tsx/.vue/.svelte/.html always-flagged, and public/site/app/pages/components/client/web prefixes). Published as plugkit v0.1.652 (2026-06-18); the dstate watcher auto-upgraded 0.1.651->0.1.652. Follow-up hardening (this session): gates.rs check_browser_witness_coverage now re-filters ledger entries through is_browser_running_file so stale pre-fix entries self-heal on watcher upgrade. Lesson: rs-plugkit (github AnEntrypoint/rs-plugkit) is the source of truth for the watcher; gm-plugkit npm is just the bootstrap; the wasm ships via AnEntrypoint/plugkit-bin GH releases keyed by Cargo.toml version.